> number of computers (and people) in the world.

The current trend is in the opposite direction.  Increasing automation
allows you to replace inefficient human interaction with ever more efficient
types of software interaction, which give huge increases overall efficiency.
Again, I don't see a hard limit until the system becomes so fast that light
speed delays are the limiting factor, and that doesn't happen until you've
gone well beyond most people's concept of a post-singularity world.

