Plants today suffer a very large chance that any given place they
might want to colonize is already occupied.  Yet they do not
follow the strategy you advise.  Instead, they send out multitudes
of cheap seeds.  The chance that each seed will take root is small,
but the cost of a seed is small enough to make the strategy work.
Advanced creatures can take a similar "shotgun" approach to
colonization.

