>instead of 4 billion,

Life is a rate-based process.  At its origin, the indirect catalysis of life 
(enzyme
makes enzyme makes ... does process) would have had to "outcompete" abiotic
processes for access to thermodynamic disequilibrium in the environment.
Slow enough and it would certainly lose.  We have no idea what the limits are,
but it's certainly possible that our own abiogenesis "barely made it".

