Biochemistry, 3rd edition, p 641-642)
It's not a problem with starvation ketosis because the body doesn't make
that many ketone bodies.  I suppose it could be a problem with Atkins-style
ketosis (more food = more ketones) but I've never heard of it; given the 
medical
community's take on Atkins that makes me think it's not a problem.
 
